               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18241028-102-person1025">
                  GEORGE 
                  PIGGOTT
               <interp inst="t18241028-102-person1025" type="surname" value="PIGGOTT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241028-102-person1025" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241028-102-person1025" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at Islington. On the 26th of September, about a quarter to nine o'clock at night, I was in <placeName id="t18241028-102-crimeloc545">Fleet-market</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18241028-102-crimeloc545" type="placeName" value="Fleet-market"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18241028-102-crimeloc545" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241028-102-off543 t18241028-102-crimeloc545"></join>, near the prison - I felt a book move in my pocket, and on turning round missed my handkerchief, and collared the prisoner with in his hand; he let it fall. I gave it to the officer. He was close behind me - two or three persons came round, and began fighting, but I kept hold of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18241028-102-person1026">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HENRY KING
               <interp inst="t18241028-102-person1026" type="surname" value="HENRY KING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241028-102-person1026" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241028-102-person1026" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in a public-house, and hearing of a robbery I went out, and found Mr. Piggott holding the prisoner.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw several persons, and went to pass them; the gentleman came up and asked if I had his handkerchief; he said he had picked it up three yards from me.</p>
